      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your feelings are valid, and it is completely understandable to feel like a hollow shell when the foundation of your self-identity was built on a lie; there is no shame in simply being honest about how broken this feels right now. However, acknowledging that part of you feels empty is not the same as erasing the person you used to be, and stopping the pretense can actually be the first step toward rebuilding a more authentic self from the ground up. Please reach out to a mental health professional who specializes in grief or existential distress to help you navigate this wreckage safely.",
      "source": "target",
